context.auth_pattern:
Analytics Platformsian API calls must use this auth pattern (token contains special characters that break curl's -u flag):
In bash: AUTH_HEADER=$(python3 -c "import base64, os; u=os.environ['ATLASSIAN_USER']; t=os.environ['ATLASSIAN_TOKEN']; print(base64.b64encode(f'{u}:{t}'.encode()).decode())")
In Python: import base64, os user = os.environ["ATLASSIAN_USER"] token = os.environ["ATLASSIAN_TOKEN"] auth = base64.b64encode(f"{user}:{token}".encode()).decode() headers = {"Authorization": f"Basic {auth}", "Accept": "application/json"}
